This paper is about deep learning for medical image analysis, specifically deformable image registration. The paper proposes an unsupervised method that uses deep neural networks to learn the spatial transformation between a pair of images. Given that the paper focuses on image analysis and deep learning, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel constraint to encourage the diffeomorphic property of the transformation, which involves optimizing the network parameters to minimize a loss function. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves optimization and regularization techniques, which could make it relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
